From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 21:17:42 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.2a: Migrate 3 directory pages to useQuery
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

First slice of the T2.2 react-query fan-out. Migrates the three
public directory pages (Investor, PML, TC) from the
useState+useEffect+manual-fetch pattern to useQuery.

Establishes the template for subsequent T2.2 sub-PRs.

Pattern used in all 3 files:

  const { data: profiles = [], isLoading } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['<Entity>Profile', { is_published: true }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.<Entity>Profile.filter({ is_published: true }),
  });

  const { data: users = [] } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['User', { role: '<role>' }],
    queryFn: () => base44.entities.User.filter({ role: '<role>' }),
    enabled: profiles.length > 0,
  });

  const userMap = useMemo(() => {
    const map = {};
    users.forEach(u => { map[u.id] = u; });
    return map;
  }, [users]);

Key improvements:
- Cache hits on revisit: directory re-renders instantly, revalidates
  in background
- 'enabled: profiles.length > 0' preserves the original optimization
  (don't fetch users if no profiles to enrich)
- useMemo replaces useState+useEffect for the lookup map (no
  synchronization bugs)
- Empty try/catch blocks gone — queryCache handles errors centrally
  (falls through to the T2.8 handler once that lands, or to the
  default react-query behavior if T2.8 isn't merged yet)
- ~30 lines of boilerplate removed per file

Files (3):
- src/pages/InvestorDirectory.jsx
- src/pages/PMLDirectory.jsx
- src/pages/TCDirectory.jsx

Deferred to subsequent T2.2 sub-PRs (T2.2b/c/d...):
- admin pages (Members, Applications, Partners, SupportTickets)
- message/service-request pages
- deal board + detail modal
- profile pages (TC/PML/Investor Profile)
- dashboard pages
- public partners page

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors, 0 warnings on touched files
- npm run build: succeeds
- Three useEffect+load functions removed; three useQuery pairs added
